President Obama and Mrs. Obama will be visiting the United Kingdom, France, Germany, and the Czech Republic from March 31 to April 5, 2009. In the UK, the President will discuss important issues with British leaders and address the global financial crisis at the London Summit. He will also engage in bilateral programs with French President Nicolas Sarkozy and German Chancellor Angela Merkel. The President will then attend NATO Summit events in France and Germany to celebrate 60 years of peace and security in Europe and discuss challenges in Afghanistan and other issues. Lastly, he will travel to the Czech Republic to meet with Czech officials and EU leaders to strengthen the partnership between the US and the EU.